{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to ask you,"},{"time":2000,"text":"what do these three people have in common?"},{"time":7000,"text":"Well, you probably recognize the first person."},{"time":9000,"text":"I'm sure you're all avid \"American Idol\" watchers."},{"time":12000,"text":"But you might not recognize Aydah Al Jahani,"},{"time":15000,"text":"who is a contestant, indeed a finalist,"},{"time":18000,"text":"in the Poet of the Millions competition,"},{"time":21000,"text":"which is broadcast out of Abu Dhabi,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and seen throughout the Arab world."},{"time":25000,"text":"In this contest"},{"time":27000,"text":"people have to write and recite"},{"time":30000,"text":"original poetry, in the Nabati form of poetry,"},{"time":33000,"text":"which is the traditional Bedouin form."},{"time":36000,"text":"And Lima Sahar was a finalist"},{"time":39000,"text":"in the Afghan Star singing competition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"Now, before I go any further,"},{"time":45000,"text":"yes, I know it all began with \"Britain's Got Talent.\""},{"time":49000,"text":"But my point in discussing this"},{"time":52000,"text":"is to show you -- I hope I'll be able to show you"},{"time":55000,"text":"how these merit-based competitions,"},{"time":59000,"text":"with equal access to everyone,"},{"time":62000,"text":"with the winner selected via voting by SMS,"},{"time":65000,"text":"are changing tribal societies."},{"time":68000,"text":"And I'm going to focus on Afghanistan"},{"time":70000,"text":"and the Arab world with the UAE,"},{"time":73000,"text":"how they're changing tribal societies,"},{"time":76000,"text":"not by introducing Western ideas,"},{"time":78000,"text":"but by being integrated into the language in those places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"It all begins with enjoyment."},{"time":87000,"text":"Video: We are late to watch \"Afghan Star.\""},{"time":90000,"text":"We are going to watch \"Afghan Star.\" We are late."},{"time":93000,"text":"We are running late."},{"time":96000,"text":"We must go to watch \"Afghan Star.\""},{"time":101000,"text":"Cynthia Schneider: These programs are reaching incredibly deeply into society."},{"time":106000,"text":"In Afghanistan, people go to extraordinary lengths"},{"time":109000,"text":"to be able to watch this program."},{"time":111000,"text":"And you don't necessarily have to have your own TV set."},{"time":114000,"text":"People watch it all over the country"},{"time":116000,"text":"also in public places."},{"time":119000,"text":"But it goes beyond watching,"},{"time":122000,"text":"because also, part of this"},{"time":125000,"text":"is campaigning."},{"time":127000,"text":"People become so engaged"},{"time":129000,"text":"that they have volunteers, just like political volunteers anyway,"},{"time":133000,"text":"who fan out over the countryside,"},{"time":136000,"text":"campaigning for their candidate."},{"time":139000,"text":"Contestants also put themselves forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"Now, of course there is a certain degree of ethnic allegiance, but not entirely."},{"time":146000,"text":"Because each year the winner has come from a different tribal group."},{"time":151000,"text":"This has opened up the door,"},{"time":153000,"text":"particularly for women."},{"time":155000,"text":"And in the last season there were two women in the finalists."},{"time":158000,"text":"One of them, Lima Sahar, is a Pashtun from Kandahar,"},{"time":161000,"text":"a very conservative part of the country."},{"time":164000,"text":"And here she relates, in the documentary film \"Afghan Star,\""},{"time":168000,"text":"how her friends urged her not to do this"},{"time":171000,"text":"and told her that she was leaving them for democracy."},{"time":174000,"text":"But she also confides that"},{"time":177000,"text":"she knows that members of the Taliban"},{"time":179000,"text":"are actually SMS-ing votes in for her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"Aydah Al Jahnani also took risks"},{"time":187000,"text":"and put herself out, to compete"},{"time":189000,"text":"in the Poet of the Millions competition."},{"time":192000,"text":"I have to say, her husband backed her from the start."},{"time":196000,"text":"But her tribe and family urged her not to compete"},{"time":199000,"text":"and were very much against it."},{"time":201000,"text":"But, once she started to win,"},{"time":204000,"text":"then they got behind her again."},{"time":206000,"text":"It turns out that competition and winning is a universal human value."},{"time":212000,"text":"And she's out there."},{"time":214000,"text":"Her poetry is about women,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and the life of women in society."},{"time":220000,"text":"So just by presenting herself"},{"time":222000,"text":"and being in competition with men --"},{"time":224000,"text":"this shows the voting on the program --"},{"time":226000,"text":"it sets a very important example for young women --"},{"time":229000,"text":"these are young women in the audience of the program --"},{"time":232000,"text":"in Abu Dhabi, but also people in the viewing audience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"Now you'd think that \"American Idol\""},{"time":238000,"text":"would introduce a measure of Americanization."},{"time":241000,"text":"But actually, just the opposite is happening."},{"time":244000,"text":"By using this engaging popular format"},{"time":247000,"text":"for traditional, local culture,"},{"time":250000,"text":"it actually, in the Gulf, is precipitating a revival"},{"time":253000,"text":"of interest in Nabati poetry,"},{"time":255000,"text":"also in traditional dress and dance and music."},{"time":259000,"text":"And for Afghanistan,"},{"time":261000,"text":"where the Taliban banned music for many years,"},{"time":265000,"text":"it is reintroducing their traditional music."},{"time":267000,"text":"They don't sing pop songs,"},{"time":269000,"text":"they sing Afghan music."},{"time":272000,"text":"And they also have learned how to lose gracefully,"},{"time":275000,"text":"without avenging the winner."},{"time":277000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":279000,"text":"No small thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"And the final, sort of, formulation"},{"time":287000,"text":"of this \"American Idol\" format,"},{"time":290000,"text":"which has just appeared in Afghanistan,"},{"time":292000,"text":"is a new program called \"The Candidate.\""},{"time":295000,"text":"And in this program, people present"},{"time":297000,"text":"policy platforms that are then voted on."},{"time":300000,"text":"Many of them are too young to run for president,"},{"time":303000,"text":"but by putting the issues out there,"},{"time":305000,"text":"they are influencing the presidential race."},{"time":307000,"text":"So for me, the substance of things unseen"},{"time":310000,"text":"is how reality TV is driving reality."},{"time":314000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":316000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}